/**********************************************************/
	Gracefully Degrading HTML5 Local Storage 
/**********************************************************/
Brett Wejrowski
The Wojo Group
thewojogroup.com
brett@wejrowski.com


This script uses four functions, save(), read(), remove(), and clear(), in order to
store name value pairs locally.  The script uses HTML5's 
localStorage when it is supported, and will use a string of
name/value pairs in cookies otherwise.  

save( "Username" , "Joe Schmoe" );

read( "Username" );  // returns "Joe Schmoe";

remove( "Username" ); // deletes data item "Username"

clear(); // deletes all local storage data
